2.1 Merge TPM and differential analysis results

# merge tables
t=merge(x = TPM , y= res_abdo, by="locus", all.x=F, all.y=T)
# order rows according to log2Fold changes
order_loci=order(t$log2FoldChange, decreasing = TRUE)
t=t[order_loci,]

2.2 Subset to candidate genes

# DE genes
t <- t[which(t$locus %in% c(candidates_abdo_down, candidates_abdo_up)),]
dim(t)
## [1] 141  39
####################################
# log2 fold #########################
####################################

log2Fold=t$log2FoldChange
summary(log2Fold)
##    Min. 1st Qu.  Median    Mean 3rd Qu.    Max. 
## -1.3300 -0.3499  0.4241  0.5244  1.2290  3.7120
# function from http://stackoverflow.com/questions/15006211/how-do-i-generate-a-mapping-from-numbers-to-colors-in-r
# to map colours
map2color<-function(x,pal,limits=NULL){
  if(is.null(limits)) limits=range(x, na.rm=TRUE)
  pal[findInterval(x,seq(limits[1],limits[2],length.out=length(pal)+1), all.inside=TRUE)]
}

categories = c(-4,-2, -1.5, -1, 0, 1, 1.5, 2, 4)
#intervals=discretize(x = log2Fold, method= "fixed", categories = c(-21,-2, -1,0, 1, 2, 20))
intervals=discretize(x = log2Fold, method= "fixed", categories = categories, onlycuts = F)
#levels(intervals)[2]="[ -5,  -2)"
#levels(intervals)[3]="[ -2,  -1)"

colours <- intervals
levels(colours)=c(map2color(x = 1:sum(categories<0), pal = colorpanel(20, low="springgreen4", high = "springgreen")), 
                  map2color(x = 1:sum(categories>0), pal = colorpanel(20, low="moccasin", high = "red")))
names(colours)=intervals


# corresponding colours
log2Fold=data.frame(intervals)
names(log2Fold)="log2Fold"
row.names(log2Fold)=t$locus

legend_log2Fold=levels(colours)
names(legend_log2Fold)=levels(intervals)
########################################

df =read.table("../data/sample_information.txt", h=T)
df = df[df$tissue=="A",-c(3,5)]
row.names(df)=df$name
df=df[,-1]

mat2=t[,grep ("A",names(t))]
df$infection=relevel(df$infection, ref = "UI")
mat2 = mat2[,order(df$infection, df$genotype)]
rownames(mat2)=t$locus

########################################
# Specify colors
########################################

ann_colors = list(
  infection = c(UI = "white", I= "grey"),
  genotype = c(G495 = "blue", Lb84 = "black",  Sienna = "red", StFoy = "green"),
  log2Fold = legend_log2Fold[nlevels(colours):1]
)

heatmap1=pheatmap(mat2, 
         color = colorRampPalette(c("navy", "white", "firebrick3"))(1500), 
         cluster_rows=F,
         cluster_cols=F,
         show_rownames=TRUE, 
         scale = "row",  
         annotation_col=df, 
         annotation_colors = ann_colors,  
         annotation_row = log2Fold, 
         main = "ABDO",
         fontsize_row=4,
        fontsize_col = 6,
        cellheight=4,
        annotation_legend=F,
        legend=F
         )
